article_title: More Employers Turn To On-Site Clinics Despite Obamacare's Cadillac Tax

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: Nearly one in three large employers have opened onsite clinics at their companies to increase access to basic primary care services despite the looming “Cadillac tax” on rich benefit plans that is triggering potential cutbacks in other health benefits. The Cadillac tax was created as part of the Affordable Care Act [...]
